{#
  Static PersistentVolume and PersistentVolumeClaim for the Zotero WebDAV
  data tree, backed by the homelab NFS share. Applied directly by zotero.yml
  before ArgoCD syncs the manifests, so the PVC exists when the Deployment
  references it as a regular volume.

  The storageClassName is set to '' and volumeName is set explicitly to force
  binding to this specific PV and prevent the default StorageClass from
  interfering. The reclaim policy is Retain so that deleting the PVC during
  development never destroys the underlying Zotero attachments — cleanup of
  the NFS export must be done explicitly.

  NFS supports ReadWriteMany, but the Deployment uses replicas=1 with a
  Recreate strategy to avoid two Apache instances mutating the same WebDAV
  tree concurrently.

  Variables:
    zotero_namespace:        Kubernetes namespace where the WebDAV server is
                             deployed.
    zotero_nfs_data_size:    Nominal size annotation for the PV and PVC.
                             NFS does not enforce quotas via PVC size.
    nfs_server_ip:           IP address of the NFS server.
    zotero_nfs_data_path:    Absolute path on the NFS server for the WebDAV
                             data tree (e.g. <nfs_k8s_path>/zotero-webdav).

  Mount options:
    soft       Instructs the kernel to return EIO after the timeout rather
               than retrying indefinitely. Allows Kubernetes to restart the
               pod and recover automatically once the NFS server is
               reachable, rather than hanging in uninterruptible D state.
    timeo=600  Initial RPC timeout in tenths of a second (60 seconds) before
               returning EIO to the calling process under soft mount
               semantics.
#}
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolume
metadata:
  name: zotero-webdav-data
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: zotero-webdav
spec:
  capacity:
    storage: '{{ zotero_nfs_data_size }}'
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  persistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain
  storageClassName: ''
  mountOptions:
    - soft
    - timeo=600
  nfs:
    server: '{{ nfs_server_ip }}'
    path: '{{ zotero_nfs_data_path }}'
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: zotero-webdav-data
  namespace: '{{ zotero_namespace }}'
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: zotero-webdav
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  storageClassName: ''
  volumeName: zotero-webdav-data
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: '{{ zotero_nfs_data_size }}'
